*iconv_set_encoding*

(PHP 4 >= 4.0.5, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

iconv_set_encoding â€” Set current setting for character encoding conversion

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  iconv_set_encoding(string $type, string $encoding): bool~

Changes the value of the internal configuration variable specified by {type} to
{encoding}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{type}

  The value of {type} can be any one of these:
   + input_encoding
   + output_encoding
   + internal_encoding

{encoding}

  The character set.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns true on success or false on failure.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 iconv_set_encoding() example

<?php >
  iconv_set_encoding("internal_encoding", "UTF-8");
  iconv_set_encoding("output_encoding", "ISO-8859-1");
<?>

